description: From the fertile mind of James Kochalka (Johnny Boo) comes an all-new fantasy adventure for all ages! We know the Dragon Puncher is an heroic warrior kitty in a robot battle-suit. But who is this new fierce fighting feline? And what outrageous adventures await on Dragon Puncher Island? Twice the punching and twice the laughs, that's for sure! Boldly combining Kochalka's signature cartooning with hilarious photography, Dragon Puncher is also a unique visual treat.

description:
Walt & Skeezix: Book Two collects the Gasoline Alley strips by the great American cartoonist Frank King from 1923 - 1924. King was the first cartoonist to have his characters age in real time and have modern storylines. In Book Two, Baby Skeezix is kidnapped, Walt's courtship with Phyllis heats up and cools down, and Walt makes a bet with his friend Avery to see who can cross the North American continent first.

There will be a new eighty-page introduction by journalist Jeet Heer exploring the strip's Chicago background and the attraction that King and other cartoonists felt for the Grand Canyon.

When Weapon Kosher, the Magic Pickle, erupts from the bedroom floor of little Jo Jo Wigman, she has to answer a lot of questions! What's the Magic Pickle's connection to the Brotherhood of Evil Produce? What is "Dill Justice?" How did Danny Johnson get to be so cute? Eisner-nominated creator Scott Morse has all the answers!

description: The Complete Wash Tubbs and Captain Easy by Roy Crane were published by the Flying Buttress Classics Library. Widely considered to be one of the first great adventure strips, Wash Tubbs the wise-cracking, girl-chasing opportunist and soldier of fortune Captain Easy are back for more fun and adventure. Volume 7 (1932-1933) reprints Crane's classic comic strips with an introduction by Bill Blackbeard. Easy's own solo adventures premiere and Crane treats his audience with breathtaking landscapes, hordes of crazed warriors, and scores of harem girls.
